<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-16T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-16T13:00:00-05:00" n="555" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.51/1545: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hood</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-16T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 16,
                                        1922—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>28. Legation’s 30, September 8, 11 a.m.</p>
                        <p>In case intimated crisis develops and Bank asks further indorsement of
                            the Liberian pledge of German liquidation funds as security <pb facs="0746" n="632" xml:id="pg_632"/> for further advances to
                            Liberian Government, you will promptly cable Bank’s proposal to the
                            Department and await instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>